        "sender_full_name": "Alexander Bentkamp",
        "timestamp": 1600083202
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, on <code>linear_algebra/char_poly/coeff</code>, we have that the minimal polynomial of a matrix divides its characteristic polynomial</p>",
        "id": 210028247,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Anderson",
        "timestamp": 1600100081
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This is not proven to be the same as the minimal polynomial of the linear transformation or anything, but it’s enough proof of concept that you could define it for linear transformations</p>",
        "id": 210028494,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Anderson",
        "timestamp": 1600100190
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Shouldn't that follow \"easily\" from the correspondence between matrices and lintrafos which is quite well-established in Lean?</p>",
        "id": 210028582,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1600100250
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Wait, I mean <code>minpoly</code> for lintrafos should make sense out of the box, right?</p>",
